reviewText: While this is not Diane Franklin's best movie, it's worth having - the character she plays is one of the most truly evil cherubic-looking teens ever (she must have had a lot of fun making it)!  Barry Bostwick and Kim Darby are excellent as the unfortunate vacationing couple who fall prey to her evil machinations. Unfortunately, like most made-for-TV movies converted to video, the pace is a bit jerky (to allow for commercials).
One of my favs a great double feature dvd set of this and The Babysitter (1980) would be great they work well together :)
I am hoping that this movie will become available for purchase. I love this movie, but can't find it anywhere. I am really hoping that this movie will be back in stock soon.
